HEADWORD: Regnant
<hw>Reg"nant</hw> <pr>(-n<it>a</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>regnans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>regnare</ets> to
reign: cf. F <ets>r⟦eacute⟧gnant</ets>. See <er>Reign</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Exercising regal authority; reigning; <as>as, a queen
<ex>regnant</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the chief power; ruling; predominant;
prevalent.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A traitor to the vices
<xex>regnant</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regnative</ent>⟦br⟧
